HEADWORD: Radiolaria
<hw>Ra`di*o*la"ri*a</hw>
<pr>(r⟦amac⟧`d⟦icr⟧*⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Radioli</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Order of
rhizopods, usually having a siliceous skeleton, or shell, and sometimes
radiating spicules. The pseudopodia project from the body like rays. It
includes the polycystines. See <er>Polycystina</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Radiolarian</ent>⟦br⟧
